bcl:definition.bcl:text:
contract of insurance means a contract of insurance between
the insurer and an insured farmer that is made under the authority of this
regulation;

crop year means the period specified in a contract of
insurance during which insurance coverage in respect of a crop or plants is
effective;

bcl:paragraph.bcl:text:
in the case of a crop of forage or plants used to grow forage, before November
              1, but, if a farmer does not apply by that date, application may be made before May 1
              of the following crop year in respect of forage seeded in that crop year;
